MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 364c2b772391e46dba637935c558b9b2, type: 3}
  m_Name: Graven_wheel_and_tiger_s_bite
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MythSO
  pageNumber: 77
  mythName: Graven wheel and tiger' s bite
  omens:
  - '1. The stars are visible, even in day, forming

    a wheel pattern, visibly
    turning.'
  - '2. A huge crater, barely the rubble of a stone

    outpost left. Heavy footprints
    within.'
  - '3. A distraught family claim a pair of great

    tigers attacked their small
    farm, eating

    their chickens, sheep, and dog. They

    claim the beasts
    fell from the sky and

    vanished back into the darkness.'
  - '4. A swathe has been cut through a forest or

    mountain. It leads toward
    the Myth Hex.'
  - '5. The Charioteer rides over the horizon,

    pulled by two great tigers. He
    is quick to

    share his past triumphs, gathering

    followers to feed his
    ego. He seeks revenge

    against the ruler of the nearest Holding,

    who
    has slighted him in a minor way.'
  - '6. Following up on a boast that somebody

    doubted, the Charioteer is preparing
    to

    charge either upstream, or into the tide,

    proving that no mere water
    is a match for

    the Chariot. They will succeed at this,

    driving the
    water away for good, before

    taking flight and returning to the stars.'
  verse: 'Omens

    1. The stars are visible, even in day, forming

    a wheel
    pattern, visibly turning.

    2. A huge crater, barely the rubble of a stone

    outpost
    left. Heavy footprints within.

    3. A distraught family claim a pair of great

    tigers
    attacked their small farm, eating

    their chickens, sheep, and dog. They

    claim
    the beasts fell from the sky and

    vanished back into the darkness.

    4.
    A swathe has been cut through a forest or

    mountain. It leads toward the
    Myth Hex.

    5. The Charioteer rides over the horizon,

    pulled by two great
    tigers. He is quick to

    share his past triumphs, gathering

    followers
    to feed his ego. He seeks revenge

    against the ruler of the nearest Holding,

    who
    has slighted him in a minor way.

    6. Following up on a boast that somebody

    doubted,
    the Charioteer is preparing to

    charge either upstream, or into the tide,

    proving
    that no mere water is a match for

    the Chariot. They will succeed at this,

    driving
    the water away for good, before

    taking flight and returning to the stars.

    Cast

    The
    Charioteer, Arayda

    VIG 16, CLA 7, SPI 18, 9 GD

    A3 (Emerald skin and
    armour)

    Meteor rod (2d8 hefty, wounded targets are

    thrown d6 Hexes,
    taking d6 further Damage)

    Driven to avenge any slights against himself

    or
    anybody he takes liking to.

    The Chariot

    5GD A2 (structure)

    2d12
    trample, nothing can stop it

    Tigers, Frecko & Parafusa

    VIG 15, CLA
    15, SPI 5, 6 GD

    Rip and tear (2d8), faster than any horse

    Hatred of
    horses, fear of mirrors.

    Bursten forth out shroud o''night'
  castEntries:
  - name: The Charioteer, Arayda
    statBlock: 'VIG 16, CLA 7, SPI 18, 9 GD

      A3 (Emerald skin and armour)'
    notes: 'Meteor rod (2d8 hefty, wounded targets are

      thrown d6 Hexes, taking
      d6 further Damage)

      Driven to avenge any slights against himself

      or
      anybody he takes liking to.

      The Chariot

      5GD A2 (structure)

      2d12
      trample, nothing can stop it'
  - name: Tigers, Frecko & Parafusa
    statBlock: 'VIG 15, CLA 15, SPI 5, 6 GD

      Rip and tear (2d8), faster than
      any horse'
    notes: 'Hatred of horses, fear of mirrors.

      Bursten forth out shroud o''night

      Graven
      wheel and tiger'' s bite

      BOASTS AND SLIGHTS

      Boast Slight

      1
      I shaped the moon It was in a past life

      2 I set stars in motion They
      disgust me

      3 I awoke the first

      Spring

      They don''t appreciate

      their
      standing

      4 I dug out the sea They mistreated a cat

      5 I rendered
      the trees

      motionless

      They squander their

      lands

      6
      I made the mountains They sleep too much

      Chariot

      Dwelling: Tranquil
      quarry ~ Sanctum: Reclusive scribes ~ Monument: Heron statue

      Hazard:
      Flooded glade ~ Curse: Dizzying reeds ~ Ruin: Smashed pottery

      Th'
  flavorTable:
    title: BOASTS AND SLIGHTS
    rows:
    - 1 I shaped the moon It was in a past life
    - 2 I set stars in motion They disgust me
    - '3 I awoke the first

      Spring

      They don''t appreciate

      their
      standing'
    - 4 I dug out the sea They mistreated a cat
    - '5 I rendered the trees

      motionless

      They squander their

      lands'
    - '6 I made the mountains They sleep too much

      Chariot'
  dwelling: Tranquil quarry
  sanctum: Reclusive scribes
  monument: Heron statue
  hazard: Flooded glade
  curse: Dizzying reeds
  ruin: Smashed pottery
  visibleByDefault: 0
  visibleMarkerPrefab: {fileID: 0}
